e in the work of such as Flaubert, Eliot, and Zola, and its continuing force in James and modernists such as Woolf. He considers also the painting of Courbet, Manet, Caillebotte, Tissot, and Lucian Freud, and such recent phenomena as "photorealism" and "reality TV."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aComparative literaturexEnglish and French. 0aComparative literaturexFrench and English. 0aEnglish fictionxHistory and criticismx19th century. 0aEnglish fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aFrench fictionxHistory and criticismx19th century. 0aFrench fictiony19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLittérature comparéexAnglaise et française. 0aLittérature comparéexFrançaise et anglaise. 0aRealism in literature. 0aRoman anglaisxHistoire et critiquex19e siècle. 0aRoman françaisxHistoire et critiquex19e siècle. 0aRéalisme dans la littérature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300127850423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300127850.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles